### AJAX

AJAX (Asynchronous JavaScript and XML) is a technique for exchanging data with a server without reloading the entire web page. It uses the XMLHttpRequest object or the Fetch API to send a request to the server and receive a response. The response is then used to update the page without a full page reload.

Here's a basic example of using AJAX to replace the contents of a page:

```javascript
// Send an AJAX request to the server
fetch('/new-url')
  .then(response => response.text())
  .then(html => {
    // Update the page with the new content
    document.getElementById('content').innerHTML = html;
  });
```

